questions.quote: You always have to know everything that's going on, don't you?
Yeah. All right. Well, do you still want to see a movie later?
Well that's the grand tour ... Aw but I save the best for last...
You wanna go out with my wife?!  Where do you get the nerve to ask me something like that?!
Well, it's not as if Susan's pregnant. You've already postponed The wedding. Who knows if you'll ever get married.
Kramer tells me that you are interested in an alternative to surgery.
Of course it was a problem for me. . . . You didn't, you didn't tell anyone else about this, did you?
Well, you should have seen it. It was quite a scene over there.
Alright, just make sure he reserves the good chair for me. Wait, what are you gonna tell him about the clanking noise in the car?
I was all primed for the first row; I was gonna put my feet up on the dugout!
